bastion_host.description: Host to use as a bastion tunnel. Can be specified with the `BASTION_HOST` environment variable.

bastion_private_key.description: File containing the bastion private key. Can be specified with the `BASTION_PRIVATE_KEY` environment variable.

bastion_user.description: User to connect to the bastion as. Can be specified with the `BASTION_USER` environment variable.

database.description: Database number. Can be specified with the `REDISDB_DATABASE` environment variable. Defaults to `0`

hostname.description: Server hostname. Can be specified with the `REDISDB_HOSTNAME` environment variable. Defaults to `127.0.0.1`

keyset.description: The keys and values of the Keyset.

port.description: Server port. Can be specified with the `REDISDB_PORT` environment variable. Defaults to `6379`

block.description: `redis_keyset` manages a list of key/val pairs in redis.
